frameDefinitions: An Entity is affected by an Event.
An Entity undergoes some change (the Event) that is (or is construed as) punctual.
A Competition comes to an end, with a Competitor tying, winning, or losing against an Opponent (or opponents) according to their Score.
An Entity ends up with some Final_quality--a new fact about the Entity.

A new Employee obtains a Position with an Employer, with which there are certain Tasks associated; in exchange for the performance of these Tasks, the Employee receives Compensation from the Employer.
The words in this frame involve an Undesirable_event which affects the Patient negatively.
frameExamples: The hotel is <t>undergoing</t> renovations at this time.
This <t>happens</t> to me all the time.
Unbelievable--he <t>lost</t> the gold medal by just .02 points!
I <t>signed</t> <t>on</t> with YouTube to make them a new GUI.
The first <t>calamity</t> was a disastrous trade war with Holland.
listRoleDefinitions: The thing which is affected by the Event.
A change in the world which affects the <fen>Entity</fen>.

This role identifies the event which occurs and affects the <fen>Entity</fen>.

The location at which the <fen>Competition</fen> takes place.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change, newly ending up in the <fen>Final_category</fen> or taking on a new <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
A description of a characteristic of the <fen>Entity</fen> after the change.
The category that the <fen>Entity</fen> ends up in after the change.  Typically, this entails taking on a number of new characteristics.
>When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
The person who enters an employment relation with an <fen>Employer</fen>.
The person (or institution) that the <fen>Employee</fen> enters an employment relationship with.
The label given to a particular type of employment.
The action that the <fen>Employee</fen> is obligated to do for the <fen>Employer</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when an <fen>Employee</fen> signs on with an <fen>Employer</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Employee</fen> enteres an employment relationship with an <fen>Employer</fen>.
The undesirable event which occurs.
The entity that experiences the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen>.
When the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> takes place.
